cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC 

The paper deals with the recognition and extension of function graphs and permutation graphs, which are both related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algorithms and complexity analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category due to the NP-completeness result presented.
